article.description: — Stanley Umude had 18 points and six rebounds as South Dakota held off UM Kansas City 66-64 on Friday night.
article.headline: Umude carries South Dakota over UM Kansas City 66-64
article.linkText: Umude carries South Dakota over UM Kansas City 66-64
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- — Stanley Umude had 18 points and six rebounds as South Dakota held off UM Kansas City 66-64 on Friday night. A.J. Plitzuweit had 14 points and seven rebounds for South Dakota (5-6, 4-2 Summit League), which won its fourth straight game. South Dakota totaled 26 second-half points, a season low for the team. Brandon McKissic had 19 points for the Roos (5-7, 1-2). Marvin Nesbitt Jr. added 13 points and 12 rebounds. Josiah Allick had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
